Durban The annual Sharks Ladies Breakfast was packed this morning as fans from the softer side gathered for a meet and greet, as well as share a joke or two and loads of selfies with Durban's rugga heroes.MC Darren Maule kept the vibe going on stage as some of the favourite players dished up some secrets and it was agreed that whatever happens at the Sharks Ladies Breakfast stays at the Sharks Ladies Breakfast&nbsp;More than 400 women attended the breakfast, hosted by FNB, at the Sibaya Casino this morning. The event is held to raise funds for the Jes Foord Foundation. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Pat&nbsp; Lambie with the ladies at his table: Picture: Tanya Waterworth &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;eThekwini deputy mayor&nbsp; Fawzia Peer with winger Lwazi Mvovo &nbsp; Picture: Tanya Waterworth &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Rowan Gouws and Garth April with May Moodley and Priya Mungal.&nbsp; &nbsp; Picture: Tanya Waterworth &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Sharks captain Philip van der Walt was in high demand .&nbsp; &nbsp; Picture: Tanya Waterworth &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Stephan Lewies does a lap dance .&nbsp; &nbsp; Picture: Tanya Waterworth &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Zeenath Hoosen and Brydie McCarthy with flanker Etienne Oosthuizen .&nbsp; &nbsp; Picture: Tanya Waterworth &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tera Mtembu enjoys the vibe. Picture: Tanya Waterworth &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; Sharks players decide on the game plan before leading the ladies out onto the dance floor . Picture: Tanya Waterworth @TheSharks @Darren Maule @FNBSA @SharksLadiesBreakfast The Independent on Saturday